“But Alison I get attached quickly so how can I manage dating (not having sex, dating) with more than one person at a time?”

1. Limit your time. If you have an hour to talk on the phone a day, each person gets 30 mins. Wrap up the call at the end of the allotted time and schedule your next call/outing.

2. Limit your outings. One date a week is more than enough time for you to get to know each person until you decide logically who’s best for you and they agree and want to commit.

And if there’s anyone who doesn’t like this approach, it’s because they don’t want to compete, which is fine! Date someone who won’t have you in a competition.

You’re not going to convince me that this technique is wrong unless you are a dating or relationship coach with more testimonials than me of happily commited engaged and married women. I’m up to 110, check my highlights❤️
